                    <comment id="12517574" author="reschke" created="Fri, 3 Aug 2007 17:43:52 +0100"  >OK, here&amp;#39;s the plan:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
- make RepositoryConfig referenceable (should we add that to the interface?)&lt;br/&gt;
- make o.a.j.s.jcrs2pi.RepositoryImpl referenceable&lt;br/&gt;
- generate references based on the RepositoryConfig&amp;#39;s reference, adding StringRefAddrs for the parameters needed by o.a.j.s.jcrs2pi.RepositoryImpl to re-create the config&lt;br/&gt;
- implement a simple ObjectFactory inside o.a.j.s.jcrs2pi.RepositoryImpl, using this information&lt;br/&gt;
</comment>
                    <comment id="12517697" author="reschke" created="Sat, 4 Aug 2007 12:27:17 +0100"  >Revision 562695: made JCR2SPI&amp;#39;s RepositoryImpl referenceable in case if the underlying RepositoryConfig instance itself is referenceable.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
I&amp;#39;ll leave the issue open for now because this may not be the final approach, and for now none of the Jackrabbit SPI contribs currently support this.&lt;br/&gt;
</comment>
                    <comment id="12518152" author="reschke" created="Tue, 7 Aug 2007 14:06:38 +0100"  >Revision 563492: enhance Javadoc with JNDI config example.&lt;br/&gt;
</comment>
                    <comment id="12552418" author="anchela" created="Mon, 17 Dec 2007 14:18:10 +0000"  >julian, is there anything else you need to do here? if not, can you resolve the issue?&lt;br/&gt;
merci&lt;br/&gt;
angela</comment>
                    <comment id="12552424" author="reschke" created="Mon, 17 Dec 2007 14:29:40 +0000"  >I think I left it open because we didn&amp;#39;t decide whether JNDI support should be optional (like it is now), or required. Since then I think we have converged on &amp;quot;optional&amp;quot;, as this reflects what we&amp;#39;re doing in JCR 2.0 as well.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Thus, I think we can close this one.&lt;br/&gt;
</comment>
                    <comment id="12552650" author="reschke" created="Tue, 18 Dec 2007 08:29:41 +0000"  >Optional JNDI support has been implemented as proposed in then initial plan.&lt;br/&gt;
</comment>
